👉 OOPs Terminology 

1. Abstraction : Hiding internal details [ Show only essential info ! ]
for example : Using this phone without bothering about how it was made.

2. Encapsulation : The act of putting various components together (in a capsule)
for example : Laptop is a single entity with wifi+speaker+storage in a single box.

In Java, encapsulation simply means that the sensitive data can be hidden from the users.

3. Inheritance : The act of deriving new things from existing things.
for example : Rickshaw --> E-Rickshaw 
              Phone ---> Smart Phone  --> (Implements DRY)

4. Polymorphism : One entity many forms
for example : Smartphone --> Phone        Smartphone ---> Calculator
here smartphone is having properties of normal phone and calculator as well

👉 Writing a custom class

We can write a custom class as follows : 

--> A Java code can have only one public class , rest will be defined without public access modifier.

class Employee{
    int id ; --------> Attribute 1
    string name;  ---------> Attribute 2
}

Any real world object = Properties + Behaviour
Object in OOPs = Atrributes + Methods

class Employee{                                                     // Creation of custom class 
    int id;
    String name;
}

public class OOPs {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("This is out custom class");
        Employee prince = new Employee();                           // Object Creation of Employee Class
        prince.id = 61;                                             // Setting Attributes of Custom Class
        prince.name = "Prince";
        System.out.println(prince.id);                              // Accessing the attributes of custom class
        System.out.println(prince.name);
    }
}

